prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Blue HUD Macro Creator Tech Poster" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Macro 3D creator-tech product hero, large and tilted, physically framed by oversized ribbed gloves or striped synthetic fingers cropped by the frame.
- Cold electric-blue and deep navy technology background with diagonal light streaks, faint grid lines, mist, bloom, and glass HUD panels.
- Large extra-bold condensed all-caps headline in white or icy gray, cropped or partly occluded behind the product.
- Translucent rounded feature cards with radial meters, pill bars, small icons, and compact technical labels.
- One warm gold or amber performance badge, used as the only major warm contrast accent.
- Glossy plastic, rubber, glass, brushed metal, beveled product edges, cyan rim light, and dramatic black shadows.
- Dense commercial product poster hierarchy with overlapping product, gloves, type, badges, and interface graphics.
- Use real-market creator hardware categories as inspiration only; do not render real brand marks or exact product replicas.

Avoid:
- {NEGATIVE_PROMPT}

Important content rule: match the extracted style first, then change the exact source content. Product categories may be camera-adjacent when requested, but all outputs must stay brandless, non-identical, and newly worded.
